Seven people were killed and five were injured after their vehicles burst into flames following a collision in Elandsfontein on New Year&rsquo;s Day, paramedics said.&ldquo;Reports from the scene indicate that the taxi and a car collided head-on before bursting into flames,&rdquo; Netcare 911 spokesperson Chris Botha said.When paramedics and firefighters arrived at the crash scene on Nettleton Road in Elandsfontein at about 07:15, they "found that both vehicles were engulfed in flames with the occupants still trapped in the wreckages.&rdquo;&ldquo;After the firefighters extinguished the flames it was found that seven people had died in the blaze,&rdquo; said Botha.Five others survived with injuries ranging from serious to minor.They were treated on the scene before being taken to hospital for further care.SOURCE:&nbsp;News24